[04:59.96]	To be the dowry of a second head,
[05:02.67]	The skull that bred them in the sepulchre.
[05:06.00]	Thus ornament is but the guiled shore
[05:09.05]	To a most dangerous sea; the beauteous scarf
[05:12.52]	Veiling an Indian beauty; in a word,
[05:15.36]	The seeming truth which cunning times put on
[05:18.90]	To entrap the wisest. Therefore, thou gaudy gold,
[05:22.58]	Hard food for Midas, I will none of thee;
[05:25.77]	Nor none of thee, thou pale and common drudge
[05:29.31]	'Tween man and man: but thou, thou meagre lead,
[05:32.78]	Which rather threatenest than dost promise aught,
[05:36.59]	Thy paleness moves me more than eloquence;
[05:39.92]	And here choose I; joy be the consequence!
[05:43.18]PORTIA	[Aside] How all the other passions fleet to air,
[05:46.79]	As doubtful thoughts, and rash-embraced despair,
[05:50.47]	And shuddering fear, and green-eyed jealousy! O love,
[05:54.42]	Be moderate; allay thy ecstasy,
[05:56.92]	In measure rein thy joy; scant this excess.
[06:00.25]	I feel too much thy blessing: make it less,
[06:03.58]	For fear I surfeit.
